Nomaswazi Nkosi Cosatu members and Venezuelan citizens living in South Africa picketing outside the United Nations Information Centre in Pretoria.&nbsp; The Venezuelan people are picketing against the Venezuelan government saying their people are dying under its leader, Nicolas Maduro.&nbsp; The Cosatu members say the Venezuelan protesters were being paid by the United States government to destabilise the Venezuelan government using South African's name.&nbsp; Cosatu says they are in full support of Maduro and Venezuela due to a long standing relationship with the country dating back to the struggle for freedom during the apartheid era.